05:49.656 --> 05:53.732
My life was a giant puzzle.

05:53.832 --> 05:58.837
I spent every day putting
the pieces together.

05:59.700 --> 06:03.808
To create the perfect picture.

06:08.778 --> 06:13.614
But then there was
a piece missing.

06:13.714 --> 06:16.234
[eerie music]

06:26.037 --> 06:31.042
And some pieces are more
important than others

06:32.043 --> 06:34.842
and we shouldn't forget that.

06:34.942 --> 06:36.534
- [Claudia] I can't remember
you ever arriving home

06:36.634 --> 06:39.640
at this time of day.

06:39.740 --> 06:42.988
- I gave myself
the afternoon off.

06:43.088 --> 06:46.716
- That's a first.

06:46.816 --> 06:49.408
- What happened to the tree?

06:49.508 --> 06:51.618
- I don't know.

06:51.718 --> 06:54.413
I missed you.

06:54.513 --> 06:59.518
Glad you came home early.

07:00.658 --> 07:05.663
- I missed you too.

07:24.302 --> 07:29.307
- Get you a glass of wine.

07:42.803 --> 07:44.947
- [Alex Voiceover] Some pieces

07:45.047 --> 07:50.052
are far more
important than others.

07:52.710 --> 07:55.129
- Is Anna back yet?

07:55.229 --> 07:57.787
I'm dying to see her.

07:57.887 --> 07:59.582
- [Claudia] Well she'll
be on the bus now.

07:59.682 --> 08:04.618
She should be back anytime.

08:05.550 --> 08:10.555
- How is school going?

08:15.077 --> 08:16.254
- Did you say something?

08:16.354 --> 08:18.839
[eerie music]

08:20.047 --> 08:21.949
- What?

08:22.049 --> 08:23.502
No, doesn't matter.

08:23.602 --> 08:24.780
- You coming through?

08:24.880 --> 08:25.880
- Yeah.

08:30.575 --> 08:34.821
[clockworks clicking
and whirring]

08:49.007 --> 08:52.635
- [Alex Voiceover] Time
is the great healer,

08:52.735 --> 08:57.706
that's what they say.

08:59.121 --> 09:03.953
But what if all the clocks
have stopped ticking?

09:05.299 --> 09:10.304
What if time's already run out?

09:15.240 --> 09:18.765
- We just have to
get through this.

09:18.865 --> 09:20.283
[intense music]

09:20.383 --> 09:22.661
[crashing]

10:05.152 --> 10:06.364
Say it.

10:06.464 --> 10:07.917
- There's nothing to say.

10:08.017 --> 10:13.022
- There's everything to
say, we just have to start.

10:13.643 --> 10:14.337
- I'm okay.

10:14.437 --> 10:15.511
- You're not okay.

10:15.611 --> 10:17.682
[crying]

10:25.483 --> 10:30.488
- I just need--
- Just need what?

10:31.213 --> 10:35.631
What do you need?

10:42.431 --> 10:47.401
- I just have to
get some air, okay?

10:59.793 --> 11:01.726
[sighs]

11:07.559 --> 11:12.564
[intense music]
[muffled screaming]

11:20.262 --> 11:22.436
[sobbing]

12:03.270 --> 12:05.483
- [Alex Voiceover] I
can still hear them.

12:05.583 --> 12:06.691
[scoffs]

12:06.791 --> 12:10.036
[wind chimes tinkling]

12:18.768 --> 12:23.014
I remember a corridor and a
stranger in a small office.

12:24.774 --> 12:27.777
I remember his few,
well-rehearsed words.

12:28.917 --> 12:30.715
[tense music]

12:30.815 --> 12:34.267
Those words
destroyed everything.

12:36.994 --> 12:38.064
My entire world.

12:47.763 --> 12:50.628
They tore down everything
I built in a heartbeat.

12:55.944 --> 12:57.048
They stole my future.

13:01.639 --> 13:04.262
I could not escape the
sound of those words.

13:06.333 --> 13:08.266
Endlessly repeating.

13:10.268 --> 13:13.378
It was then that I
knew I was truly--

13:13.478 --> 13:15.653
[smashes]

13:16.723 --> 13:19.381
[geese honking]

13:35.431 --> 13:38.158
[wings flapping]

13:41.265 --> 13:42.265
But then

13:44.958 --> 13:46.373
as I listened very hard

13:49.411 --> 13:51.447
I could hear another
sound on the breeze.

13:53.553 --> 13:55.420
[gentle piano music]

13:55.520 --> 13:56.694
A sound calling me home.

13:59.421 --> 14:01.492
A sound that might give
me a second chance.

14:03.045 --> 14:05.358
[chuckling]

14:11.260 --> 14:12.917
Was there a second chance?

14:27.069 --> 14:28.729
- That sounds great.

14:28.829 --> 14:29.972
[strikes discordant chords]

14:30.072 --> 14:33.282
- We both know that
sounded horrible.

14:34.732 --> 14:35.460
[gentle piano music]

14:35.560 --> 14:36.665
- Oh, it was good!

14:38.253 --> 14:39.292
[tense music]

14:39.392 --> 14:41.811
You just have to keep going.

14:41.911 --> 14:43.399
You can't just give up.

14:43.499 --> 14:48.504
- When things get hard,
yes, I know Daddy.

14:49.402 --> 14:50.402
- But it's true.

14:52.370 --> 14:55.515
And you've got so much
better these last few months.

14:55.615 --> 14:56.650
- No I haven't.

14:58.204 --> 14:59.204
- You have.

15:01.138 --> 15:03.036
So I guess I'm not
getting a hug then,

15:04.762 --> 15:06.936
since I haven't seen
you in over two weeks.

15:09.215 --> 15:10.699
- It's been longer than that.

15:12.701 --> 15:13.943
I hardly see you.

15:15.083 --> 15:16.256
You're always working.

15:17.809 --> 15:18.809
- I know.

15:20.605 --> 15:21.886
I'm here now.

15:21.986 --> 15:22.986
The whole weekend.

15:25.162 --> 15:28.755
- And then you won't
be back for ages.

15:28.855 --> 15:31.340
- That'll change, you'll see.

15:33.963 --> 15:36.069
How about that hug?

15:44.940 --> 15:47.049
[chuckles]

15:47.149 --> 15:48.149
- You're cold.

15:50.014 --> 15:51.467
Why are you so cold?

15:51.567 --> 15:53.051
- It was chilly by the lake.

15:57.401 --> 16:01.270
You go finish your practice
and then we'll eat, okay?

16:01.370 --> 16:02.370
- Okay.

16:03.648 --> 16:04.963
- Very good.

16:05.063 --> 16:09.067
[gentle discordant piano music]

16:11.242 --> 16:12.242
- How was the walk?

16:13.969 --> 16:14.969
- It was good.

16:32.677 --> 16:34.472
Why does she hate
the piano so much?

16:36.198 --> 16:38.135
- Have you lost the
power of hearing?

16:38.235 --> 16:40.133
She hates it because
she's shit at it.

16:41.307 --> 16:43.312
- It was your idea
she should start.

16:43.412 --> 16:45.694
- Oh, let's rewind there.

16:45.794 --> 16:47.903
It was your idea
she should start.

16:48.003 --> 16:50.147
- Was it?
- Mm hmm.

16:50.247 --> 16:55.252
- Huh, well, now it's my idea
that she should fucking stop.

16:57.599 --> 16:59.432
I mean listen to that.

16:59.532 --> 17:01.813
- I listen to that all the time.

17:01.913 --> 17:03.570
It's lucky I'm
not on medication.

17:06.332 --> 17:07.332
- Anna!

17:09.990 --> 17:11.371
That's fine now darling.

17:14.132 --> 17:16.031
You can go and do
your homework, okay?

17:18.344 --> 17:20.348
- [Anna] Ugh, thank god!

17:20.449 --> 17:22.489
[laughing]

17:22.589 --> 17:23.421
[thunder rumbling]

17:23.521 --> 17:24.521
- There's a storm coming.

17:34.429 --> 17:35.429
- Yeah.

17:45.578 --> 17:49.478
How would you feel about
us selling the piano?

17:52.481 --> 17:53.481
- Are you serious?

17:55.139 --> 17:55.971
- Yeah.

17:56.071 --> 17:57.731
- What about not giving up?

17:57.831 --> 18:00.834
- In this case, give up.

18:02.008 --> 18:03.630
- Thanks, Daddy.
- You're welcome.

18:05.736 --> 18:07.427
What are you doing?
- Maths.

18:08.497 --> 18:09.916
- Maths?

18:10.016 --> 18:12.850
Phew.

18:12.950 --> 18:16.094
[flapping lips]
[laughs]

18:16.194 --> 18:17.437
I'm crap at maths.

18:20.060 --> 18:21.548
Your mum's very good.

18:21.648 --> 18:24.931
[thunder rumbling]
[tense music]

18:25.031 --> 18:26.274
- There's a storm coming.

18:28.068 --> 18:29.315
A big one.

18:29.415 --> 18:30.415
- It'll pass.

18:31.417 --> 18:32.417
Don't worry.

18:52.886 --> 18:54.163
- My tree died.

18:56.787 --> 18:57.787
- Yeah, I know.

19:00.791 --> 19:01.791
Sorry.

19:04.553 --> 19:06.659
- It's bad luck when
a rowan tree dies.

19:08.108 --> 19:09.213
Rowans protect us.

19:11.353 --> 19:13.945
- What does it protect us from?

19:14.045 --> 19:15.119
- Bad things.

19:15.219 --> 19:16.638
[suspenseful music]

19:16.738 --> 19:17.946
- [Alex] What bad things?

19:21.329 --> 19:22.675
- You know what, Daddy.

19:32.581 --> 19:34.859
- [Alex] I can't believe
you still have this.

19:36.344 --> 19:37.762
- It's the first thing
you ever bought me.

19:37.862 --> 19:39.661
- Is it?

19:39.761 --> 19:41.349
- [Anna] He isn't
going anywhere.

19:44.869 --> 19:45.943
[chuckles]

19:46.043 --> 19:48.290
- Anyway, you
finish your homework

19:48.390 --> 19:51.048
and we'll go and eat,
I'm starving, eh?

19:52.808 --> 19:54.016
Mummy's made a surprise.

19:57.261 --> 19:59.612
I'll go and get changed.

19:59.712 --> 20:01.334
- [Anna] Don't you
know what's coming?

20:04.164 --> 20:05.164
- What?

20:13.070 --> 20:15.628
Here.
- Okay.

20:15.728 --> 20:17.871
[speaking in foreign language]

20:17.971 --> 20:18.700
- Wow.

20:18.800 --> 20:20.253
[laughs]

20:20.353 --> 20:21.392
You spoil us.

20:21.492 --> 20:24.257
- You don't deserve
my ingenious.

20:24.357 --> 20:25.603
- Yes we do.

20:25.703 --> 20:27.981
[laughing]

20:28.879 --> 20:30.367
Thanks babe.

20:30.467 --> 20:32.507
- Here you go.
- Looks amazing.

20:32.607 --> 20:34.129
- Thank you.

20:34.229 --> 20:35.368
- Mm, wow this is nice.

20:36.334 --> 20:37.753
Sorry, I should have waited.

20:37.853 --> 20:38.853
- It's fine, eat.

20:39.821 --> 20:40.821
But first,

20:42.789 --> 20:43.789
to a great weekend.

20:44.860 --> 20:45.589
- To a great weekend.
[glasses clinking]

20:45.689 --> 20:47.038
- To a great weekend.

20:47.138 --> 20:49.386
[laughing]

20:49.486 --> 20:52.420
- And your mother, she just
doesn't start sometimes.

20:53.662 --> 20:55.699
- [Claudia] Don't listen to him.

20:58.356 --> 21:00.051
- Oh that wine really is lovely.

21:00.151 --> 21:01.501
Can I have some more Claudia?

21:01.601 --> 21:05.333
- Is that a please or?
- It's a definite please.

21:05.433 --> 21:06.161
Wow.

21:06.261 --> 21:09.195
[thunder rumbling]

21:10.127 --> 21:13.855
[house rumbling and shaking]

21:19.861 --> 21:21.794
What the hell was that?

21:23.589 --> 21:24.589
- What is it?

21:26.523 --> 21:27.523
- It's nothing.

21:29.146 --> 21:33.430
Just let me take
a look, it's fine.

21:33.530 --> 21:37.054
[thunder rumbling]

21:37.154 --> 21:40.157
[suspenseful music]

21:49.925 --> 21:52.790
[thunder rumbling]

21:54.033 --> 21:56.104
- Jesus Christ, what is that?

21:58.624 --> 21:59.659
- It's a storm.

22:01.143 --> 22:02.044
[laughs]

22:02.144 --> 22:03.144
- Are you fucking kidding me?

22:04.077 --> 22:05.078
That's an explosion.

22:09.117 --> 22:10.117
What do we do?

22:12.051 --> 22:13.262
- If it were an explosion

22:13.362 --> 22:15.368
we wouldn't be stood
here talking about it,

22:15.468 --> 22:17.301
we'd be dead already.

22:17.401 --> 22:18.401
- Then what is it?

22:19.437 --> 22:21.750
- I told you, it's just
a storm, it'll pass.

22:27.653 --> 22:29.071
Go and see Anna.

22:29.171 --> 22:31.277
Tell her the Russians
are still in Russia.

22:52.505 --> 22:54.338
- It is just a storm, honey.

22:54.438 --> 22:55.438
It'll be gone soon.

22:59.201 --> 23:00.617
Gonna check the weather, okay?

23:23.605 --> 23:26.888
[suspenseful music]

23:26.988 --> 23:28.265
- What is this?

23:35.928 --> 23:37.485
- Daddy!

23:37.585 --> 23:40.280
Daddy, you have to come in!

23:40.380 --> 23:43.111
- It's just a storm,
honey, go inside.

23:43.211 --> 23:45.562
- You have to come
in, it's Mummy.

23:45.662 --> 23:50.080
Something's wrong with her,
she's in the dining room.

23:57.674 --> 23:59.058
[sobbing]

23:59.158 --> 24:00.128
- What's wrong?

24:00.228 --> 24:02.544
[intense music]

24:02.644 --> 24:04.957
[screaming]

24:07.407 --> 24:08.654
Hey, tell me, what's--

24:08.754 --> 24:10.172
[sobs]

24:10.272 --> 24:11.001
What is it?

24:11.101 --> 24:12.101
Hey, shh.

24:13.103 --> 24:14.103
What?

24:15.139 --> 24:18.180
- We just have to
get through this.

24:18.280 --> 24:19.009
- Get through what, darling?

24:19.109 --> 24:19.941
- Whatever happens.

24:20.041 --> 24:21.943
- Hey, hey, hey, it's okay.

24:22.043 --> 24:23.600
Just shh, shh, shh.

24:23.700 --> 24:25.218
- I don't know what comes next.

24:26.634 --> 24:28.221
I don't know what happens to us!

24:30.223 --> 24:33.264
- I don't know what you're
talking about, come on, hey.

24:33.364 --> 24:34.364
Hey.

24:35.194 --> 24:37.061
- No!
- Come on.

24:37.161 --> 24:40.061
- We can't just keep pretending
that this isn't happening!

24:43.064 --> 24:45.307
- Shh, it's okay.

24:46.723 --> 24:47.723
- I'm fine.

24:51.900 --> 24:52.629
I'm fine.

24:52.729 --> 24:54.320
I'm fine.

24:54.420 --> 24:57.285
Just give me a minute.

25:00.391 --> 25:01.391
- Mummy.

25:10.194 --> 25:12.338
- It's alright, eh.

25:12.438 --> 25:13.511
Come Anna.

25:13.611 --> 25:14.611
It's okay darling.

25:15.683 --> 25:17.205
It's alright.

25:17.305 --> 25:22.037
Mummy's just had a bad day.

25:22.137 --> 25:23.137
- I made her cry.

25:25.658 --> 25:26.386
- What?

25:26.486 --> 25:27.318
What do you mean?

25:27.418 --> 25:29.148
Why did you make her cry?

25:29.248 --> 25:30.698
- You know why, Daddy.

25:34.632 --> 25:39.054
- I love you.

25:39.154 --> 25:42.261
[light bulb fizzles]

25:43.365 --> 25:44.365
Let's get a torch.

25:45.126 --> 25:46.821
Should we get a torch?

25:46.921 --> 25:49.237
Come on, let's get a torch.

25:49.337 --> 25:51.822
[eerie music]

26:07.010 --> 26:08.010
Those are all fine.

26:10.358 --> 26:13.261
Let's find Mum.

26:13.361 --> 26:16.295
[thunder rumbling]

26:26.581 --> 26:27.893
Are you alright?

26:32.483 --> 26:36.487
What did you mean before, you
don't know what comes next?

26:38.282 --> 26:39.490
- You know what I meant.

26:42.804 --> 26:46.984
What's wrong with you?

26:47.084 --> 26:48.879
You know exactly what I meant.

27:00.235 --> 27:03.135
[thunder rumbling]

27:05.827 --> 27:08.485
[door creaking]

27:11.350 --> 27:12.903
- Anna, close the door.

27:20.359 --> 27:21.359
Anna.

27:37.721 --> 27:38.721
Everything's died.

28:04.921 --> 28:06.754
You go through to the
lounge, wait there.

28:06.854 --> 28:08.203
We'll be through in a minute.

28:08.303 --> 28:09.857
- I don't want to.
- Just go.

28:14.206 --> 28:15.207
I have to call someone.

28:21.351 --> 28:22.351
Oh shit.

28:23.077 --> 28:23.840
Have you got your phone?

28:23.940 --> 28:25.289
- It's in the kitchen.

28:25.389 --> 28:26.739
Who are you calling?

28:26.839 --> 28:29.328
- I don't know,
the fucking police?

28:29.428 --> 28:31.119
You go through and
see she's okay.

28:54.039 --> 28:56.113
[phone ringing]

28:56.213 --> 28:58.733
[eerie music]

29:00.769 --> 29:01.670
Hello?

29:01.770 --> 29:04.121
Hello?
[static buzzing]

29:04.221 --> 29:06.572
- [Man] You know
what this is about.

29:06.672 --> 29:07.672
- I'm sorry?

29:09.502 --> 29:11.888
- [Man] There isn't
long left now.

29:11.988 --> 29:13.265
Only a short time to go.

29:15.474 --> 29:17.855
You know where you are
and what you have to do.

29:18.995 --> 29:21.483
You have to listen to me.

29:21.583 --> 29:25.591
You have to listen to her.

29:25.691 --> 29:26.691
- Hello?

29:30.661 --> 29:31.493
Hello?

29:31.593 --> 29:36.326
Fuck.

29:36.426 --> 29:37.426
Anna.

29:38.531 --> 29:42.435
Oh for fuck's sake.

29:42.535 --> 29:44.675
Anna, Anna.

29:46.919 --> 29:48.269
Anna.

29:48.369 --> 29:51.306
[suspenseful music]

29:51.406 --> 29:52.614
You have to come inside.

29:55.238 --> 29:56.791
- Something's out there, Daddy.

29:59.069 --> 30:00.381
Under those clouds.

30:04.454 --> 30:05.869
I know you can't see it yet.

30:07.629 --> 30:08.630
It's not your fault.

30:10.667 --> 30:12.186
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

30:14.326 --> 30:18.019
- It's out there.

30:19.089 --> 30:20.089
It won't go.

30:23.335 --> 30:25.306
[shivers]

30:25.406 --> 30:26.407
I'm so cold.

30:27.615 --> 30:29.272
- Come on darling,
let's go, please.

30:31.619 --> 30:33.828
I said let's go back
inside the house.

30:35.864 --> 30:37.073
Anna, go, now!

30:38.005 --> 30:39.005
Now!

30:40.076 --> 30:41.076
Go.

30:47.255 --> 30:48.255
What have they done?

31:00.165 --> 31:01.963
We need to stay inside.

31:02.063 --> 31:03.896
Are all the doors
and windows closed?

31:03.996 --> 31:04.996
- Yeah.

31:07.896 --> 31:09.829
- I think there's
something in the air.

31:14.248 --> 31:16.598
Should we brighten
this place up a bit?

31:16.698 --> 31:18.807
Should we light some candles?

31:18.907 --> 31:20.395
Yeah.

31:20.495 --> 31:21.495
Come on then.

31:22.635 --> 31:23.912
- I'll be in the kitchen.

31:25.190 --> 31:26.191
- You okay?
- Yeah.

31:30.402 --> 31:33.857
[lighter clicking]

31:33.957 --> 31:35.786
- [Anna] She knows
why the tree died.

31:39.790 --> 31:40.790
- What do you mean?

31:41.930 --> 31:43.518
- Can't you see
what's happening?

31:46.314 --> 31:47.314
Out there?

31:48.454 --> 31:50.077
- It's just a storm, darling.

32:05.471 --> 32:07.546
Ice cream, what a good idea.

32:07.646 --> 32:09.513
- Of course, want some?

32:09.613 --> 32:10.342
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

32:10.442 --> 32:11.895
- Not you.

32:11.995 --> 32:13.721
I'm just gonna talk
to Dad for a minute.

32:16.931 --> 32:18.243
What did the police say?

32:19.416 --> 32:21.453
- The phones are down,
I couldn't get through.

32:22.902 --> 32:25.046
There's no internet,
there's nothing.

32:25.146 --> 32:26.768
- I heard you
talking to someone.

32:28.391 --> 32:29.292
- No.

32:29.392 --> 32:30.392
That was nothing.

32:32.153 --> 32:33.503
- Then we have to
try and get help.

32:33.603 --> 32:35.332
- We can't go out there yet.

32:35.432 --> 32:36.432
You've seen it.

32:37.572 --> 32:39.402
I think something's
poisoned the air.

32:41.162 --> 32:42.167
We have to wait.

32:42.267 --> 32:43.202
- Wait for what?

32:43.302 --> 32:44.648
It'll get into the house.

32:49.274 --> 32:50.482
- You alright sweetheart?

32:51.655 --> 32:52.655
- I'm cold.

32:55.349 --> 32:57.320
- Well then the
ice cream probably

32:57.420 --> 32:58.938
wasn't a good idea then, was it?

33:00.112 --> 33:01.769
Shall I get you
a warmer sweater?

33:04.116 --> 33:06.291
- Where is Mummy?
- I'm here, sweetheart.

33:11.710 --> 33:12.710
Is that good?

33:14.747 --> 33:16.649
- I'm cold though.

33:16.749 --> 33:17.754
- Ah.

33:17.854 --> 33:19.373
- I'll go and get her a sweater.

33:20.926 --> 33:23.273
- [Anna] You were never
there when I needed you.

33:28.520 --> 33:29.520
- What?

33:30.901 --> 33:31.901
What did you say?

33:35.389 --> 33:37.394
- I didn't say anything.

33:37.494 --> 33:38.494
- She didn't speak.

33:48.919 --> 33:49.855
- [Anna] Daddy, it hurts!

33:49.955 --> 33:52.444
[intense music]
- Anna?

33:52.544 --> 33:54.170
- [Anna] Daddy I need you here!

33:54.270 --> 33:56.172
- Anna!

33:56.272 --> 33:57.276
Anna!

33:57.376 --> 33:58.860
- [Anna] Daddy, it hurts!

34:01.035 --> 34:01.936
- What?

34:02.036 --> 34:03.213
Why are you shouting?

34:03.313 --> 34:04.313
She's here.

34:05.488 --> 34:06.903
- I just heard her up there.

34:08.629 --> 34:11.014
[intense music]

34:11.114 --> 34:12.049
- Daddy.

34:12.149 --> 34:13.703
- No--
- It hurts so much.

34:17.672 --> 34:18.672
What's wrong, Daddy?

34:22.815 --> 34:27.203
- Alex, what is it?

34:27.303 --> 34:28.580
- I'm sorry.

34:33.757 --> 34:34.757
I'm not feeling well.

34:35.449 --> 34:36.657
- That's how it started.

34:38.279 --> 34:39.279
- What?

34:41.524 --> 34:42.908
How what started?

34:43.007 --> 34:45.496
- I love you.

34:45.597 --> 34:47.875
I always will.

35:12.624 --> 35:15.872
- Mummy?
[suspenseful music]

35:15.972 --> 35:18.285
[screaming]

35:20.356 --> 35:22.565
[shouting]

35:25.982 --> 35:27.328
What's Mummy doing now?

35:30.227 --> 35:32.368
[sobbing]

35:33.369 --> 35:36.786
- You stay in here, do not move.

35:52.319 --> 35:55.222
Claudia, what the
hell are you doing?

35:55.322 --> 35:56.844
- The fucking tree!

35:56.944 --> 35:59.295
That's why all
this is happening.

35:59.395 --> 36:00.572
I don't want this

36:00.672 --> 36:03.951
fucking piece of shit
in my garden anymore!

36:05.401 --> 36:06.129
Ah!

36:06.229 --> 36:07.334
- Stop, stop!

36:08.300 --> 36:09.132
Stop!

36:09.232 --> 36:11.479
- It was supposed to protect us!

36:11.579 --> 36:13.136
- Stop!
[screaming]

36:13.236 --> 36:14.724
Stop!

36:14.824 --> 36:17.554
I didn't come back here
to see you like this!

36:17.654 --> 36:18.654
- Come back?

36:21.969 --> 36:23.077
What do you mean?

36:23.177 --> 36:24.454
- I don't know what
I fucking mean!

36:25.869 --> 36:28.565
We can't be out here,
we have to be inside!

36:28.665 --> 36:30.222
Anna's there!

36:30.322 --> 36:31.875
- She's not in the house!

36:33.152 --> 36:34.502
- What?

36:34.602 --> 36:37.156
- Did you not hear what they
said to us in that room?

36:38.330 --> 36:42.023
Did you not hear
what has to happen?

36:44.923 --> 36:48.344
- I don't know what the
fuck you are talking about!

36:48.444 --> 36:49.586
What room?

36:49.686 --> 36:51.174
What fucking room?

36:51.274 --> 36:53.310
- You can't pretend
this isn't happening.

36:54.553 --> 36:55.834
You have to face it.

36:55.934 --> 36:57.629
[thunder rumbling]

36:57.729 --> 36:59.765
[crying]

37:15.402 --> 37:16.472
- Anna, Anna?

37:24.928 --> 37:27.275
[cork pops]

37:50.264 --> 37:51.545
I need to look for Anna.

37:51.645 --> 37:54.924
- She's not here
you fucking idiot!

37:57.513 --> 37:59.342
If you won't go with
me, that's fine.

38:00.619 --> 38:01.619
But I have to go.

38:03.519 --> 38:05.282
- Go with you where?

38:05.382 --> 38:06.767
I don't know what you mean!

38:06.867 --> 38:10.564
- For fuck's sake, Alex!
- What's happening to you?

38:10.664 --> 38:12.669
You can't go out there!

38:12.769 --> 38:13.769
I've told you!

38:18.913 --> 38:20.294
- There's nothing I can do.

38:21.709 --> 38:23.193
But I still have to be there.

38:24.160 --> 38:26.645
[tense music]

38:41.246 --> 38:43.559
[car beeps]

39:01.369 --> 39:03.237
- [Alex] Where are you going?

39:03.337 --> 39:06.309
- I can't look after
both of you right now.

39:06.409 --> 39:07.583
I can't do this anymore.

39:09.274 --> 39:10.274
I have to be there.

39:12.311 --> 39:13.520
- We've done this before.

39:14.762 --> 39:16.281
You've said this to me before.

39:17.282 --> 39:18.283
Where are you going?

39:46.276 --> 39:48.696
I didn't come back here
to see you like this!

39:48.796 --> 39:50.560
- [Claudia] Come back,
what do you mean?

39:50.660 --> 39:52.766
- [Alex] I don't know
what I fucking mean!

40:08.436 --> 40:09.576
- Why did she leave us?

40:12.164 --> 40:14.028
- She's gone to get
help, I told you.

40:14.891 --> 40:16.931
- Why didn't we go with her?

40:17.031 --> 40:19.033
- Because it's better
that we stay here.

40:22.865 --> 40:23.865
- Why?

40:27.352 --> 40:30.010
[intense music]

40:34.773 --> 40:35.773
- Anna.

40:37.707 --> 40:38.777
Come and hold my hand.

40:39.813 --> 40:42.229
- Why?
- Just do it, now.

40:49.892 --> 40:50.620
[screaming]

40:50.720 --> 40:55.691
- It's him!

40:57.658 --> 40:59.039
- Wait here, hold that.

40:59.971 --> 41:01.351
- Don't go near him, Daddy!

41:05.217 --> 41:06.217
Daddy!

41:07.461 --> 41:10.395
[thunder rumbling]

41:12.397 --> 41:14.054
- Not here, come on.

41:15.400 --> 41:19.131
Down into the cellar.
- I hate it down there!

41:19.231 --> 41:21.406
- [Alex] Quickly, quickly.

41:22.407 --> 41:23.515
- I don't wanna go down there.

41:23.615 --> 41:25.928
- [Alex] Please go down
quick, do as I say.

41:37.318 --> 41:38.595
- I'm freezing.

41:39.631 --> 41:40.770
- You're gonna be fine.

41:49.606 --> 41:51.405
- He's gonna come
down here, Daddy.

41:51.505 --> 41:54.684
- No, we're safe here.

41:54.784 --> 41:57.166
[whimpering]

41:58.788 --> 41:59.788
It's okay.

42:00.825 --> 42:02.865
It's okay, darling.

42:02.965 --> 42:06.316
[banging]
[intense music]

42:06.416 --> 42:07.935
- The ax won't hurt him, Daddy.

42:18.049 --> 42:19.291
- I know what this is.

42:24.020 --> 42:24.956
Look at me.

42:25.056 --> 42:27.993
- Dad.
- Look at me.

42:28.093 --> 42:29.093
Look at me.

42:29.785 --> 42:31.479
Concentrate, keep looking at me.

42:31.579 --> 42:34.206
We can make this go away,
we can make this go away.

42:34.306 --> 42:36.036
We can make him go away.

42:36.136 --> 42:37.658
If you just keep looking at me.

42:37.758 --> 42:38.897
Look at me, look at me.

42:40.209 --> 42:42.387
We can make this
go away, we can.

42:42.487 --> 42:44.006
Just keep looking at me.

42:45.593 --> 42:46.593
You see?

42:47.803 --> 42:48.803
Okay?

42:56.432 --> 42:57.432
- He's gone.

42:58.606 --> 43:00.474
But he's going to come back.

43:00.574 --> 43:02.718
- No he's not.

43:02.818 --> 43:03.788
I promise.

43:03.888 --> 43:07.067
Let me have a look, okay?

43:07.167 --> 43:12.172
Okay?
- Okay.

43:30.086 --> 43:31.086
- Anna.

43:33.400 --> 43:34.400
Anna?

43:36.334 --> 43:37.338
Anna?

43:37.438 --> 43:39.924
It's okay darling, he's gone.

43:41.753 --> 43:42.753
Anna?

43:44.376 --> 43:45.726
Anna!

43:45.826 --> 43:48.484
[intense music]

43:49.416 --> 43:50.317
Anna!

43:50.417 --> 43:52.043
Anna!

43:52.143 --> 43:53.143
Anna!

43:57.217 --> 43:58.252
Sweetheart, Anna?

43:59.495 --> 44:00.495
Sweetheart?

44:09.022 --> 44:10.022
Anna?

44:21.379 --> 44:22.379
That's beautiful.

44:26.522 --> 44:27.522
Who's that?

44:28.869 --> 44:29.869
- A stranger.

44:31.907 --> 44:33.498
- [Alex] What stranger?

44:33.598 --> 44:35.569
[suspenseful music]

44:35.669 --> 44:39.815
- I don't know, but
I don't like him.

44:39.915 --> 44:42.438
- Then why did you draw him?

44:42.538 --> 44:44.371
- [Anna] I'm drawing
it how it is.

44:44.471 --> 44:47.512
The clouds come
first, then he comes.

44:47.612 --> 44:49.479
- What does he want?

44:49.579 --> 44:52.448
- You know what he wants.

44:52.548 --> 44:57.553
You know what he wants.

45:59.580 --> 46:03.381
Daddy!

46:03.481 --> 46:08.486
Daddy!

46:12.386 --> 46:15.044
[door creaking]

46:45.005 --> 46:48.736
[intense music]
- Anna?

46:48.836 --> 46:49.836
Anna?

46:50.666 --> 46:51.666
Anna!

46:54.014 --> 46:55.014
Anna!

46:55.740 --> 46:56.740
Baby.

46:59.088 --> 47:00.088
Are you okay?

47:00.814 --> 47:01.814
Can you speak?

47:02.954 --> 47:04.335
- It hurts so much.

47:05.439 --> 47:07.269
- What hurts,
darling, what is it?

47:09.236 --> 47:10.236
- My tummy.

47:10.927 --> 47:11.927
- Your tummy?

47:13.413 --> 47:14.521
Can...

47:14.621 --> 47:16.450
Well let's get you
out of here, shall we?

47:17.555 --> 47:19.039
Come on darling, can you move?

47:20.316 --> 47:22.356
Come on darling, here we go.

47:22.456 --> 47:24.462
Put your arms 'round
me, there you go.

47:24.562 --> 47:25.632
Come on, up you go.

47:27.703 --> 47:30.399
Okay.

47:30.499 --> 47:32.953
- [Anna] I heard a
voice whispering.

47:33.053 --> 47:34.368
- You did?

47:34.468 --> 47:37.782
- [Anna] He told me I
didn't belong here anymore.

47:40.095 --> 47:44.616
He didn't take me, he
just, just left me.

47:45.859 --> 47:47.002
[thunder rumbling]

47:47.102 --> 47:48.620
- Well that's because
you belong with me.

47:51.071 --> 47:53.970
And I'll never, ever let you go.

47:55.248 --> 47:56.248
Okay?

47:57.836 --> 47:59.873
[crying]

48:01.668 --> 48:03.984
Come on, that's it, you're okay.

48:04.084 --> 48:05.158
You're okay darling.

48:05.258 --> 48:06.849
Just lie there a second.

48:06.949 --> 48:08.057
Okay?

48:08.157 --> 48:09.300
That's it.

48:09.400 --> 48:11.716
Just stay there for a
second, you're okay.

48:11.816 --> 48:12.817
Okay darling.

48:13.749 --> 48:16.407
[phone ringing]

48:23.655 --> 48:24.556
Hello?

48:24.656 --> 48:25.902
- [Claudia] Alex.

48:26.002 --> 48:27.728
- Hello?
- Alex.

48:28.971 --> 48:30.076
- Claudia?
- Yeah.

48:31.905 --> 48:36.706
I'm here, I just saw
her, she's sleeping.

48:36.806 --> 48:37.984
- Who?

48:38.084 --> 48:39.882
- [Claudia] Anna,
who do you think?

48:39.982 --> 48:41.090
- Well Anna's here with me!

48:41.190 --> 48:42.574
- [Claudia] What are
you talking about?

48:42.674 --> 48:43.674
- She's sick!

48:44.711 --> 48:46.130
I have to get her out of here!

48:46.230 --> 48:47.230
We can't stay here.

48:51.994 --> 48:53.068
Come on.

48:53.168 --> 48:54.552
Come on baby.

48:54.652 --> 48:58.832
That's it, up you go, come
on, that's it, let's go.

48:58.932 --> 49:00.834
[thunder rumbling]
[suspenseful music]

49:00.934 --> 49:03.354
Alright darling, you'll be fine.

49:03.454 --> 49:05.045
Let's get you in here.

49:05.145 --> 49:06.736
Okay darling.

49:06.836 --> 49:08.359
You're gonna be fine.

49:08.459 --> 49:10.119
You're gonna be fine, okay?

49:10.219 --> 49:15.224
There you go.

49:18.124 --> 49:20.954
[engine rumbling]

49:29.997 --> 49:32.759
[haunting music]

49:59.095 --> 50:00.095
What is this?

50:04.549 --> 50:05.549
The road.

50:08.070 --> 50:09.175
There's only one road.

50:11.798 --> 50:13.455
All the other roads have gone.

50:39.170 --> 50:41.590
- You need to go back
to the house, Daddy.

50:41.690 --> 50:42.898
- We can't go back there.

50:46.695 --> 50:47.695
- Not me.

50:48.973 --> 50:49.973
You.

50:51.320 --> 50:52.320
You need to go back.

50:56.049 --> 50:58.948
[suspenseful music]

51:19.521 --> 51:21.971
Not we, you.

51:25.492 --> 51:28.426
[thunder rumbling]

52:29.245 --> 52:32.252
- Come on darling, it's okay.

52:32.352 --> 52:34.354
Come on sweetheart.

52:43.605 --> 52:45.503
- [Anna] What is
this place, Daddy?

52:46.401 --> 52:48.268
- I don't know, sweetheart,

52:48.368 --> 52:50.995
but we have to find some help.

52:51.095 --> 52:52.095
Hello?

52:53.200 --> 52:54.792
Is there anyone there?

52:54.892 --> 52:56.134
Can someone help me?

52:57.204 --> 52:58.204
Hello?

53:06.144 --> 53:07.145
Here we are.

53:08.561 --> 53:09.669
There you go.

53:09.769 --> 53:11.774
It's alright, sweetheart.

53:11.874 --> 53:12.874
Just sleep.

53:15.222 --> 53:18.778
[footsteps tapping softly]

53:27.131 --> 53:28.339
Excuse me, sorry.

53:35.760 --> 53:36.760
Hello?

53:37.624 --> 53:39.077
- Yes sir, how can I help you?

53:39.177 --> 53:41.632
- Is this a hospital?

53:41.732 --> 53:42.805
- Of course, sir.

53:42.905 --> 53:43.737
How can I help?

53:43.837 --> 53:45.360
- My daughter, she's sick.

53:45.460 --> 53:47.983
- Yes sir, she's
with the doctors now.

53:48.083 --> 53:49.916
- No I'm sorry, I don't
think you understand,

53:50.016 --> 53:51.435
we've just come in.

53:51.535 --> 53:53.502
My daughter is here,
we need your help.

53:54.572 --> 53:55.572
Please, listen.

54:02.235 --> 54:03.235
Anna?

54:04.099 --> 54:05.311
My daughter was just there.

54:05.411 --> 54:06.446
Where is my daughter?

54:07.827 --> 54:09.207
Where has my daughter gone?

54:11.037 --> 54:12.870
- The doctors are
with her now, sir.

54:12.970 --> 54:14.872
Just take a seat and the
doctors will be along

54:14.972 --> 54:15.973
to talk to you soon.

54:17.146 --> 54:20.533
- I said where have
they taken her?

54:20.633 --> 54:22.638
- She'll have gone to
the sixth floor, sir.

54:22.738 --> 54:24.913
I'm sure the doctors
will talk to you soon.

54:25.845 --> 54:28.848
[suspenseful music]

54:57.566 --> 54:59.019
[intense music]

54:59.119 --> 55:00.642
[shouting]

55:00.742 --> 55:02.364
- Get the fuck off!

55:08.404 --> 55:09.404
Anna!

55:10.337 --> 55:12.205
Anna, where are you?

55:12.305 --> 55:13.305
Get down!

55:15.895 --> 55:17.590
- Alex, keep calm.

55:17.690 --> 55:18.694
It'll all be over soon.

55:18.794 --> 55:22.526
- No!

55:22.626 --> 55:24.148
- [Anna] Daddy!

55:24.248 --> 55:26.806
Get them off me!

55:26.906 --> 55:29.291
Stop them, Daddy!

55:29.391 --> 55:32.190
They're hurting me!

55:32.290 --> 55:34.814
Daddy, Daddy!

55:34.914 --> 55:38.089
[breathing shallowly]

56:05.738 --> 56:07.981
[clanking]

56:11.640 --> 56:13.918
[grunting]

56:19.337 --> 56:21.995
[intense music]

56:23.479 --> 56:25.240
- Get me out of this!

56:26.413 --> 56:28.692
Get me fucking out of this!

56:37.459 --> 56:38.459
Claudia?

56:40.704 --> 56:41.704
Claudia?

